                            <comment id="13423606" author="grace.huang" created="Fri, 27 Jul 2012 01:10:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See the code implementation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; void reportTablesInFlux() {
    AtomicInteger numSkipped = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; AtomicInteger(0);
    HTableDescriptor[] allTables = getTables(numSkipped); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; allTables == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;    errors.print(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt; of Tables: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + allTables.length); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; Null pointer exception here&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&apos;d better to check if (allTables == null)  to avoid that NPE.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13424688" author="ram_krish" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 04:24:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per the recent code changes I remember a NPE was fixed while getting the tables.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 HTableDescriptor[] htd = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HTableDescriptor[0];
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I could see this change in  getHTableDescriptors().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13424696" author="grace.huang" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 04:53:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes. you are right. It is the issue for 0.94.0 only. thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427079" author="grace.huang" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 02:31:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that the problem has already been solved in 0.94 branch. We can close this bug entry. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
